The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	Panaji, Oct. 24 (PTI): An oil tanker carrying 6,000 litres of highly inflammable aviation fuel overturned on the Goa airport runway yesterday, forcing its partial closure and affecting operations.           
	The runway was shut down for two and half hours last night after the Indian Oil Corporation tanker toppled on its way towards civil terminal to refuel a parked aircraft. Only 5,700ft of the 8,000ft runway is operational now.                  
	New Delhi: The National Advisory Council (NAC), headed by UPA chairperson Sonia Gandhi, has recommended that the government take steps in co-ordination with states to end the shameful practice of manual scavenging by March 2012.                  
	Jammu (PTI): An army jawan was injured when Pakistani troops opened fire this evening on an Indian post in Jammu and Kashmirs Poonch, the third instance of ceasefire violation in a month. The firing lasted for over an hour.                                                                                                                                              
